                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Memorandum in response to the Italia/n ambassadors
                        communication of a telegram dated October 19 received by him, from the
                        Italian minister for foreign affairs.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-10-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 19, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Minister Conger has not yet answered our inquiry in the categorical form
                    indicated in the telegram of the Marquis Visconti-Venosta.</p>
                <p>Upon his general response, this Government is instructing him that while the list
                    of the culpable persons given in the Chinese edict of September 25 may be taken
                    as a basis, the foreign ministers in Pekin may designate additional names to the
                    negotiations.</p>
            </div>
